entry.def: If you give someone or something the go-ahead, you give them permission to start doing something.

example.ex: The Greek government today gave the go-ahead for five major road schemes...
example.tran: 希腊政府今天批准了5项重大的道路修建方案。

example.ex: Don't do any major repair work until you get the go-ahead from your insurers.
example.tran: 除非经保险公司同意，否则不要进行任何大修。

entry.tran: 有进取心的；具有开拓精神的
entry.def: A go-ahead person or organization tries hard to succeed, often by using new methods.

example.ex: Fairview Estate is one of the oldest and the most go-ahead wine producers in South Africa.
example.tran: “丽景庄园”是南非历史最悠久、最具创新精神的酿酒商之一。
